interpretation_guidance: Proposed model: Continuous-time ODE with E1/E2/E3 extensions. Linear/Coulomb: Assume constant discharge rate (ignores voltage nonlinearity). Scheduled shutdown: Android 'Bedtime mode' forces sleep 23:00-07:00 (+15% TTE). iOS Low Power Mode: Aggressive throttling (+18% TTE but -40% performance).
Mid-SOC: Peukert effect visible. Linear/Coulomb overestimate by 6%. Scheduled shutdown less effective (user active hours). iOS LPM maintains 15% gain.
Low-SOC: Voltage drop accelerates. Linear/Coulomb error reaches 13.5%. Proposed model captures nonlinear R(SOC). Scheduled shutdown marginal (<1h gain). iOS LPM: 13.6% better.
Critical zone: Linear/Coulomb catastrophically fail (40% error). Internal resistance R(SOC) dominates. Scheduled shutdown: +24% (user tolerates delays). iOS LPM: +16% (but blocks background tasks).
